        <svcsubproc id="s305010706.15.3">
            <title>ECT Operational Diagnostics</title>
            <figure id="f305010760" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/J31240.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Continuous Monitor session</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury, use care to prevent contact with the door edge when the cab is up
                        and the door is open.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use EST, select D_ContinuousMonitor.ssn from the Open Session File window, select Open
                    to open the session.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f305010761" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/J31046.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Continuous Monitor test</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Select Diagnostics from the menu bar.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Select Key-On Engine-Off Tests from the drop down menu.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">From the KOEO Diagnostics menu, select Continuous Monitor and select Run to start the
                    test.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Monitor ECT signal voltage. Verify an active DTC for the ECT circuit.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If code is active, do step 8 and 9 to check circuit for the ECT sensor using the
                    following table.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury, death, including damage to the engine or vehicle, be careful around
                        rotating parts (belts and fan) and hot engine surfaces.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Wiggle connectors and wires at all suspected problem locations. If circuit continuity is
                    interrupted, the EST will display DTCs related to the condition.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect engine harness from temperature sensor.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Inspect connectors for damaged pins, corrosion, or loose pins. Repair if necessary.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect Temperature Sensor Breakout Harness to engine harness only.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f305010762" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/J31087.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Close session</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When finished with this test, select Session from menu bar, then Close.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>After removing connector, inspect for damaged pins, corrosion, or loose terminals. Repair as
                        required.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t3050107130" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Circuit Checks - ECT Sensor</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.39in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.77in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="3.00*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>Use EST, breakout harness, 3-Banana Plug Harness, and 500 ohm resistor harness.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>Test Condition</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                                <para>Spec</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3" align="center">
                                <para>Checks</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Sensor disconnected</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>> 4.6 V</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If voltage less than 4.6 volts, check signal circuit for short to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>3-Banana Plug Harness connected between Pin 2 (Green) and Pin 1 (Black) of
                                    breakout harness
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>0 V</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If voltage is greater than 0.127 volts, check ground and signal circuit for open
                                    or high resistance. Use a breakout box and measure resistance from Pin 1 to Pin X1-6
                                    and from Pin 2 to X1-8 (spec &#60; 5 &#x2126;).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>500 Ohm resistor harness connected between Pin 2 (Green) and Pin 1 (Black) of
                                    breakout harness
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60; 1.0 V</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If voltage is greater than 1.0 volts, check signal circuit for short to V
                                    <subscript>REF</subscript>, B+, or another sensor's signal voltage.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>Connect engine harness to sensor. Use the EST to clear DTCs. If an active code
                                    remains after checking test conditions, replace the ECT sensor.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s305010706.15.4">
            <title>ECT Pin-Point Diagnostics</title>
            <figure id="f305010763" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/J31061.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"/>
                <caption>ECT circuit diagram</caption>
            </figure>
            <table id="t3050107131" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Voltage Checks - Sensor Connector</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.05in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.10in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="3.00*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>Turn ignition switch to OFF. Disconnect harness from sensor. Inspect for bent pins
                                    or corrosion. Connect breakout harness to engine harness only. Turn ignition switch
                                    to ON.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Test Point</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Spec</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>2 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>4.6 to 5.0 V</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Pull up voltage, if no voltage or low, circuit is open, has high resistance, or
                                    short to ground
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>1 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>0 to 0.25 V</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Voltage greater than 0.25 volts, wire shorted to V
                                    <subscript>REF</subscript>
                                    or B+.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para></para>
            <figure id="f305010764" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/J31061.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"/>
                <caption>ECT circuit diagram</caption>
            </figure>
            <table id="t3050107132" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Resistance Checks - Connector to Chassis Ground</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.05in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.10in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="3.00*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <warning>
                                    <para>To avoid personal injury, death, including damage to the engine or vehicle,
                                        always disconnect main negative battery cable first. Always connect the main
                                        negative battery cable last.
                                    </para>
                                </warning>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>Turn ignition switch to OFF. Disconnect harness from sensor. Connect ECT breakout
                                    harness to engine harness only. Disconnect negative battery cable.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>Test Point</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                                <para>Spec</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3" align="center">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>1 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>&#60; 5 &#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>If greater than 5 &#x2126;, check for open ground circuit</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>2 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>> 1 k&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>If less than 1 k&#x2126;, check for shorted signal to ground</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <table id="t3050107133" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Harness Resistance Checks</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.05in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.10in"/>
